<div class='communityAnswer'>
<div class='communityAnswerBody'>
<div class='answererUserIcon'>
<a class="leftAlignedImage userPhoto" href="/user/show/51228073-jasmine-perkovic"><img alt="" src="https://i.gr-assets.com/images/S/compressed.photo.goodreads.com/users/1495775506i/51228073._UX100_CR0,16,100,100_.jpg" /></a>
</div>
<div class='communityAnswerTextContainer'>
<span class='communityAnswererName'>
<a href="/user/show/51228073-jasmine-perkovic">Jasmine Perkovic</a>
</span>
<span class='communityAnswerText'>
<div class='spoiler'>
This answer contains spoilers…
<span class='spoilerAnswerText'>
<a class="jsShowSpoiler spoilerAction">(view spoiler)</a><span class="spoilerContainer" style="display: none">[
  
    For me, it is before John Coffey's execution when he is telling Paul Edgecombe that he wants to go (die). He talks about being in pain, feeling lonely<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">…more</a>
    For me, it is before John Coffey's execution when he is telling Paul Edgecombe that he wants to go (die). He talks about being in pain, feeling lonely, being "tired of people been ugly to each other" (491), wanting to help but not being able to, and being in the dark. It was heartbreaking reading about a man who was going to be executed for a crime he did not commit want to die and then say (his last words) "I'm sorry for what I am" (507).<a href="#" rel="nofollow noopener">(less)</a>
  
 <a class="jsHideSpoiler spoilerAction">(hide spoiler)</a>]</span>
</span>
</div>
</span>
</div>
