        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/3606765827?book_show_action=true">Apr 08, 2021</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Derrick" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Derrick" href="/user/show/93081346-derrick">Derrick</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="it was amazing"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">it was amazing</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span></span>

          <span class="greyText">&nbsp;&middot;&nbsp;</span>
          <a class="lightGreyText" title="Kindle Edition " href="/book/show/8269071-the-green-mile">review of another edition</a>


        

          <div class="uitext greyText bookshelves">
            Shelves:
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/93081346-derrick?shelf=unowned-king-books">unowned-king-books</a>, 
              <a class="actionLinkLite" href="/review/list/93081346-derrick?shelf=king-books">king-books</a>
          </div>
    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3606765827" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer3019613687405469530"><strong>Amazing Story</strong><br/><br/>This book has some of the best writing I&apos;ve ever read. The narrative is just so sincere and modest. All the characters, both good and bad, are so captivating. This is the kind of story that will remain with me for ages. This book has it all; humor, sorrow, regret, elation, rage, and of course there&apos;s some paranormal aspects. I&apos;ve been a fan of the film adaptation forever. I actually think I did myself a bit of a disservice being so familiar with the story. This was my first time rea</span>
  <span id="freeText3019613687405469530" style="display:none"><strong>Amazing Story</strong><br /><br />This book has some of the best writing I've ever read. The narrative is just so sincere and modest. All the characters, both good and bad, are so captivating. This is the kind of story that will remain with me for ages. This book has it all; humor, sorrow, regret, elation, rage, and of course there's some paranormal aspects. I've been a fan of the film adaptation forever. I actually think I did myself a bit of a disservice being so familiar with the story. This was my first time reading it and I felt like I would have had stronger reactions to certain parts if I wasn't already so familiar with the story. If I have one small complaint, it would be I felt like it got a little preachy towards the end. Overall this is an extraordinary story. I'd recommend it to anyone looking for a well-rounded book.</span>
  <a data-text-id="3019613687405469530" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


