        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer3451060187" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer17766455870369244651">just finished reading 𝕿𝖍𝖊 𝕲𝖗𝖊𝖊𝖓 𝕸𝖎𝖑𝖊 by stephen king. this is my first book ever by him and I really couldn&apos;t have picked a better choice. the amount of emotions I felt while reading this 😭😭 this story was so emotional, funny, unfair and cute and so many other things... there were times I actually tried to force myself not to cry lmao. I fell in love with Mr. Jingles, his cute tricks, even though I&apos;m well terrified of mice 😂 as for Paul, if I was him, I would&apos;ve quit the job because of John Coff</span>
  <span id="freeText17766455870369244651" style="display:none">just finished reading 𝕿𝖍𝖊 𝕲𝖗𝖊𝖊𝖓 𝕸𝖎𝖑𝖊 by stephen king. this is my first book ever by him and I really couldn't have picked a better choice. the amount of emotions I felt while reading this 😭😭 this story was so emotional, funny, unfair and cute and so many other things... there were times I actually tried to force myself not to cry lmao. I fell in love with Mr. Jingles, his cute tricks, even though I'm well terrified of mice 😂 as for Paul, if I was him, I would've quit the job because of John Coffey (I won't say why, you gotta read it). I'm gonna miss Paul, Brutal, Dean, Harry and even Percy, the biggest jerk I've ever read about in a book lol. I still haven't watched the movie adaptation, guess it's about time for me to do so.</span>
